Denel employees received just a fifth (20 percent) of their salaries in May. The armoured-car and artillery manufacturer last paid workers in full a year ago. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - It's unclear where Denel will get the R500-million to pay workers their outstanding salaries. National Union of Mineworkers coordinator, Mawonga Madolo, says the union has been told the board is resolving the matter. READ: Treasury says Denel needs R500m to tackle liquidity challenges He says the situation is so critical that some workers have resorted to taking their lives. The union has now issued a letter of demand to the parastatal.